      <category domain="https://www.devjev.nl/categories/how-to/">How To</category>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;With this post I want to share a lazy and a hacky way for finding the Azure DevOps &lt;code&gt;Project Id&lt;/code&gt; of any project in your Azure DevOps Organization.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;heading-element&#34; id=&#34;the-lazy-api-query&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;The lazy API query&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;#the-lazy-api-query&#34; class=&#34;heading-mark&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;svg class=&#34;octicon octicon-link&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 16 16&#34; version=&#34;1.1&#34; width=&#34;16&#34; height=&#34;16&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z&#34;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;It can feel a bit daunting to start using Azure DevOps API. But what most folks are not aware of is that data retrieval API&amp;rsquo;s can be queried using&#xA;your favorite browser.&#xA;To get the &lt;code&gt;Project Id&lt;/code&gt; we can do this with the projects &lt;code&gt;LIST&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;GET&lt;/code&gt; API&amp;rsquo;s.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
